== Separation of Shinto and Buddhism, and Haibutsu Kishaku == The [[Meiji Restoration]] brought about the [[Shinbutsu bunri|separation of Shinto and Buddhism]] and the [[Haibutsu kishaku|abolition of Buddhism]]. In 1869 (Meiji 2), the temples of {{ill|Ashikuraji|ja|芦峅寺|12=draft|12=draft}} and Iwakuraji were forced to close and reorganized into [[Oyama Shrine]]. Furthermore, the {{ill|Tateyama Shugendō|ja|立山修験|12=draft|12=draft}} rituals, such as the Nunobashi Grand Consecration, and the dissemination of Tateyama Gongen worship were prohibited.
